Test Branch 1.0.816?? Test 2026-01-22

This update contains a major systems upgrade. The engine has been upgraded to Unity 6.3 and the graphics rendering code reworked.
Bugs are expected, please refer to the Known Issues list below and report any other issues you encounter via the in game bug report system.

Known Issues

Portrait Age Interpolation is not working and has been disabled regardless of the player setting
General icons are partially hidden behind unit icons
City widget production icons can be obscured by water
Tile visibility can flash on and off
Timeline screen does not always render fog of war correctly
Volcano display issues
Brightness/Contrast issues

Design

Adjustments to Family Archetype character tendencies:
Champions have more Zealots and less Heroes
Riders have more Heroes and less Zealots
Improvements to Carthage campaign persistency

Programming

Unity updated from 2022.3 to 6.3
Graphics code converted to Unity's Universal Rendering Pipeline
The URP upgrade improves graphics performance, letting the game render with fewer draw calls and use fewer shader variants

UI

Restart Game button renamed Reroll Game. This keeps the same map and preserves nation/dynasty of random AI opponents but now rerolls the random seed
New Map button renamed to Reroll Map. This button is not shown for games on predefined maps
Valid Improvements, Rural, and Urban worker filters show improvements valid anywhere in the city rather than just for current tile
Character XP is now shown when they have upgraded at least once but progress to next level is 0


Bugs Fixed

Fixed character peak legitimacy including previous leader's ending legitimacy. "Legitimacy" in the HoF tooltip now "Final Legitimacy"
Fixed Bulwark Cuirass UI issue
Fixed Unyielding Banner reassigning general to non-player units
Fixed scores not updating after effectPlayers change
Fixed event decisions not getting restored after clearing selection
Fixed tutorial videos not showing in the encyclopedia on Linux
Fixed Wrath of Gods scenario warnings
